Package extended_mitre.cwe

Class CWEobject

  • java.lang.Object
    • extended_mitre.cwe.CWEobject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    @Entity(name="cwe")
public class CWEobject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a CWE object (CWE code (ID), name of weakness, abstraction attribute, structure attribute, ...)

    It can parse CWE weakness objects from given XML file

    Objects can be put into database

    It also can create a CWE object from given parameters and return it

    Author:
    Tomas Bozek (XarfNao)

      • CWEfileToArraylist

        public static java.util.List<CWEobject> CWEfileToArraylist​(java.lang.String cwe_file,
                                                           java.util.List<CAPECobject> capec_objs,
                                                           java.util.List<CWEextRefObj> ext_refs)
        This method's purpose is to parse and create a List of CWE weakness objects from given XML file which contains them and to make connections with the right CAPEC objects

        It uses DOM XML parser

        It goes through file that contains latest list of CWE weaknesses, parses them and returns them in a List

        Parameters:
        cwe_file - path to .xml file with CWE data
        capec_objs - existing CAPEC objects for search of the relating ones
        ext_refs - existing CWE External Reference objects for search of the relating ones
        Returns:
        List of CWE weakness objects from given XML file

      • CWEintoDatabase

        public static void CWEintoDatabase​(java.util.List<CWEobject> cwe_objs,
                                   org.hibernate.SessionFactory sf)
        This method's purpose is to put all CWE objects and their relations into database
        Parameters:
        cwe_objs - List of all parsed CWE objects
        sf - object needed to get hibernate Session Factory and to work with database
